issuesFound.explanation:
The `inlineValidator.bind()` calls attach validation rules but only use `srUtils.markInvalid()` which adds `aria-describedby`. It never sets `aria-invalid="true"` on the input when validation fails, violating WCAG 4.1.2.  
  Fix (apply to each bound field, e.g., newsletter email):  
  ```js
  // Line 5110 – after inlineValidator.bind(_emailEl, ['required','email']);
  _emailEl.addEventListener('blur', () => {
    const result = inlineValidator.validate(_emailEl);
    if (!result.valid) {
      setAttr(_emailEl, 'aria-invalid', 'true');
    } else {
      removeAttr(_emailEl, 'aria-invalid');
    }
  });
  ```

